{"tid":1360765,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"【南華早報】英國親中新首相莊漢生尤感興趣於一帶一路","createTime":"2019-07-24T12:18:06.000Z","updateTime":"2019-07-24T13:07:12.000Z","uid":105924,"like":0,"dislike":23,"uniUserReply":6,"replies":[{"pid":"0e00b0f7ff893f5fe16b518b6c7089531ff73058","tid":1360765,"uid":105924,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-07-24T12:18:06.000Z","msg":"各位應該唔駛再旨意英國政府會為香港問題出一分力，因為香港問題本身就係削弱英中關係既其中議題，而脫歐本身就令英國減少對歐盟市場既依賴，其真空必由中國所填補，所以莊漢生會好似首相金馬倫咁儘量避開香港議題，以尋求同中國有更緊密既商貿關係。<br />\n<br />\n&lsquo;Pro-China&rsquo; Boris Johnson &lsquo;enthusiastic&rsquo; about belt and road plan<br />\nBritain&rsquo;s next prime minister welcomes Chinese investment and students to &lsquo;most open economy in Europe&rsquo;<br />\nJohnson tells Chinese-language broadcaster: &lsquo;We are very interested in what President Xi is doing&rsquo;<br />\n<br />\n<span style=\"color: red;\"><strong>Boris Johnson, Britain&rsquo;s prime minister-designate, said his government would be very &ldquo;pro-China&rdquo;, in an interview with a Hong Kong-based Chinese-language broadcaster shortly before he was chosen to succeed Theresa May on Tuesday.</strong></span><br />\nSpeaking to Phoenix TV, Johnson backed Chinese President Xi Jinping&rsquo;s infrastructure-based Belt and Road Initiative and said his government would maintain an open market for Chinese investors in Britain.<br />\n&ldquo;We are very enthusiastic about the Belt and Road Initiative. We are very interested in what President Xi is doing [for the plan],&rdquo; he said.<br />\nThe Brexit campaigner also vowed to keep Britain as &ldquo;the most open economy in Europe&rdquo; for Chinese investments. &ldquo;Don&rsquo;t forget [we are] the most open international investment [destination], particularly [for] Chinese investment. We have Chinese companies coming in to do Hinkley, for instance, the big nuclear power plant.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3019884/pro-china-boris-jo